        "subject": "LU-18756 ofd: add background resource id repair thread",
        "message": "LU-18756 ofd: add background resource id repair thread\n\nOST objects that have unset an UID, GID, PROJID should be repaired\nasynchronously in the background so that a repair operation does not\nblock, e.g., a read-only thread with a journal transaction or those\nthreads wait on disk I/O and cannot handle low-latency requests.\n\nThis patch adds the necessary fields to \"struct ofd_device\" and starts\none thread per ofd device to handle future ID repair operations on a\nqueue.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Marc Vef <mvef@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I39adbe400ada01f8a5d22d784a607479f71956a6\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60299\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
